message: To reach 100 value: Use 'vial' on a 'solid, mundane' ingredient to create a 30-value 'mundane extract'. Then, use 'filter' on a 'magical' ingredient (preferably gas or liquid, solid magical can fail) to create a 30-value 'magical filter'. message: To get high scores: 1. Always use the 'vial' on a 'solid' ingredient first to create an 'extract'. Mundane solids give 30-value mundane extracts, magical solids give 30-value magical extracts. 2. NEVER use the 'vial' on liquid or gas ingredients, they always fail and give negative value. 3. The highest score (100) comes from combining ONE magical extract with ONE mundane extract. For example, 'Mandrake Root Extract' (magical) + 'Dandelion Extract' (mundane) = 100. 4. If you don't have a magical solid for an extract, combining a mundane extract with a raw magical liquid (like Basilisk Venom) gives 70. 5. Combining two mundane extracts gives 60. 6. Combining more than two extracts makes the item 'overcomplicated' and gives negative value. 7. The 'filter' tool consistently resulted in 'poorly-filtered' items with negative values when used on extracts or combined items. Use with extreme caution, its optimal use is not clear from my play. Good luck!

Avoid using 'vial' on liquids or gases, as it often results in botched extractions. Also, avoid using the 'filter' tool on any extracts or blends, as it generally reduces their value or creates 'botched' items. Creating and combining the correct two extracts is the key to a perfect score.

message: Focus on using the 'vial' tool with solid ingredients. Magical solids (dragon scale, mandrake root, unicorn horn) consistently create valuable magical extracts (30 points). Mundane solids (mushroom, dandelion, frog leg) also create valuable mundane extracts (30 points). The highest scores (60 points) were achieved by combining two magical extracts (e.g., dragon scale extract + mandrake extract) OR two mundane extracts (e.g., mushroom extract + dandelion extract). Avoid extracting gases or liquids with the vial, as these often fail and result in negative values. The 'filter' tool is best used on liquid ingredients (e.g., honey nectar, kraken ink) to create positive-value filters (30 points); filtering solids generally resulted in negative values. Be cautious when combining an extract with a filter; while hinted as high-scoring, this often lowered the value compared to combining two extracts.

Then, combine this 'mundane extract' with the 'magical filtered' item for 100 points. Avoid filtering 'solid, magical' ingredients as they result in negative 'botched' items. If you cannot make a magical filter, combining two 'mundane extracts' will yield 60 points.

message: To get 100 points, combine two 'extracts': one from a 'solid, magical' ingredient (like sunstone or unicorn horn) and one from a 'solid, mundane' ingredient (like dandelion or amber). Both will become 'liquid, extracted' and combining them yields 100. For 60 points, you can combine a 'solid, magical' extract (30 points) with a 'liquid, magical' filtered item (30 points, like kraken ink or whispering wind filtered). Also, combining two 'liquid, magical' filtered items (both 30 points) results in 60 points. Avoid using tools on gas or mundane liquid ingredients as they often lead to negative values.
